'''The camel's nose''' is a [[metaphor]] for a situation where the permitting of some small act will lead consequently to a larger undesireable act or circumstance.

The root phrase usually attributed to be a saying of Arabs, or middle eastern cultures, roughly as follows:
:''Do not allow a camel to put his nose under the edge of your tent, for soon you will have a camel in your tent.''

